Instruction: Using the inspection panel, probe the DC voltage over time at (1) the node between the light sensor and its comparator input and (2) the comparator output node that feeds the relay‑drive stage, each with respect to the control‑module ground. Observe for the ~20 s oscillation or excursions toward the rails and note whether either node drops or changes state in synchrony with the lamp’s brief turn‑off events.
